    "patient_text_brief": "His eyes and face started looking yellow about 3 weeks ago (around day 5–7 after he was born). It's mostly just in the eyes and face – not on his chest, belly, arms, or legs. It got a bit more noticeable in the first 2 weeks, but now it seems to be slowly getting better.\n\nHe is exclusively breastfed, feeds really well 8–10 times a day, and is gaining weight nicely. He poops normal yellow color several times a day and pees clear/pale normally. No fever, no vomiting, no poor feeding – he's active and happy most of the time.\n\nHe was born full term by normal delivery, cried right away, no NICU, no problems during pregnancy or birth. My baby boy Mohd. Ahzad is 4 weeks old now. I'm his mom (first-time), and I'm really worried about this yellow color not going away fully. I haven't given any medicines or stopped breastfeeding. Please help, doctor saab – is this serious?",
